<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">Someone gave the very good advice of getting yourself a quest from the first person inside the Wholeseller guild. That way you get XP and cash for what you do anyways. I haven't done that but wish I had.
<br />

<br />
Yesterday I dinged 40 in mining. This means I can mine in Antonica for Iron. I need that for my new inks. I will actively pursue to get all my collecting skills to 40. I got a quest to make 10 pants in my scholar guild. Therefor I could as well get a collect 15 pelts quest in Wholessers guild as well. I also need roots for my other componants in making cloth for the pants.
<br />

<br />
Get the Wholeseller quest before you collect in earnest.
<br />

<br />
Raw basil is bugged and do not have a recepie for converting to basil. All else can be used. My main trouble is inventory space. This is what I have done. As soon as I have collected one stack of fish I run back to skill.
<br />

<br />
Buy 20 salts, 20 peppers and 20 coals. Combine them to 20 packets of spice. Buy 20 coal and start combining fish/frog legs and try to carry only one stack at a time in back pack. Inventory space is dear.
<br />

<br />
I concentrated most of my efforts towards making my own spells. I now concentrate my efforts to make stacks of items that I will need. Until I can go for the end result I try to put the subcombines in the bank.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
